This paper’s allegation is direct:

When a private AI executive repeatedly says that public access to powerful AI creates catastrophic risk, while his own private company continues building and deploying powerful AI, he is not merely describing risk. He is lowering the character of everyone outside his institution.

The injury is not abstract. It affects who is trusted, who is regulated, who receives funding, who is allowed to publish, who is presumed reckless, and who is treated as morally fit to build intelligence systems.

