4. The Method of Defamation

The defamation does not operate by saying:

“Martin Ollett is dangerous.”

It operates by saying:

“People outside our controlled institutional environment are dangerous.”

This is more effective than a direct insult because it avoids naming the injured person while still damaging the category to which he belongs.

