8. The Evidence Gap Against Open Builders

The U.S. NTIA reviewed open-weight foundation models in 2024 and recommended monitoring risks, but not restricting currently available open model weights. It specifically recognised that open-weight models allow small companies, researchers, nonprofits, and individuals to build on and adapt AI systems.  

The UK AI Security Institute has acknowledged both sides: open-weight systems increase transparency, red teaming, innovation, and reduced market concentration, while also posing risks because safeguards can be removed and models can be modified for harmful purposes.  

That is the appropriate evidentiary position: risk exists, benefits exist, more evidence is needed, and targeted governance is required.

It is not evidence for a blanket moral conclusion that open builders are reckless.

It is not evidence that ordinary people are unsafe.

It is not evidence that Anthropic is morally entitled to stand above the public.

